-- Greenfield Partners Starts European Real Estate Loan Servicing
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-10-10T12:43:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/greenfield-partners-starts-european-real-estate-loan-servicing.html
Greenfield Partners LLC, a South
Norwalk, Connecticut-based real estate fund manager, started a
business providing European commercial real estate loan
servicing in partnership with Raith Capital Partners.  Paul Lloyd, Ravi Joseph and Bill Sexton will lead the
business, according to a statement today. Lloyd has been head of
CBRE’s servicing unit since 2009, Joseph was Morgan Stanley’s
European head of securitization until 2004 and he has since
worked with Sexton at Mount Street Capital.  Greenfield owns a majority interest in Clayton Holdings
LLC, which provides due diligence on  mortgage loans . Loan
servicers earn fees for managing mortgages on behalf of
bondholders and private equity firms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
 pkuo2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
